      <description>&lt;p&gt;For a long time the only way to launch &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linuxfoundation.org/&#34;&gt;Linux&lt;/a&gt; commands in &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/windows&#34;&gt;Windows&lt;/a&gt; was with &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cygwin.com/&#34;&gt;Cygwin&lt;/a&gt;. But &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cygwin.com/&#34;&gt;Cygwin&lt;/a&gt; is rather bulky and can take a long time to download if you are on a slower Internet connection.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As I&amp;rsquo;ve mentioned &lt;a href=&#34;https://valticus.pro/tags/linux/&#34;&gt;before&lt;/a&gt;, I love &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linuxfoundation.org/&#34;&gt;Linux&lt;/a&gt; for its stability and reliability. So I was looking for a simpler way to execute Linux commands in &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/windows&#34;&gt;Windows&lt;/a&gt;, and found it!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I present to you &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/bmatzelle/gow/wiki&#34;&gt;GNU on Windows&lt;/a&gt; also known as &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/bmatzelle/gow/wiki&#34;&gt;GoW)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To quote GoW&amp;rsquo;s website:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
